{"name": "jwt-auth-provider", "metadata": {"name": "jwt-auth-provider", "version": "0.1.2", "classifiers": ["Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/Dhruv7201/auth", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["fastapi", "passlib", "pyjwt"], "summary": "JWT authentication package for FastAPI", "upload_time": 1735813927}, "documentation": ["\n# JWT Auth for FastAPI\n\nThis is a simple JWT authentication package for FastAPI that provides:\n\n- JWT token creation\n- Token verification and decoding\n- Password hashing and verification\n- FastAPI dependency injection for secure endpoints\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install jwt-auth-provider\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### 1. Create a token:\n\n```python\nfrom jwt_auth.auth import create_access_token\n\n# Create a JWT token\naccess_token = create_access_token({\"sub\": \"username\"}, secret_key, algorithm)\n```\n\n### 2. Use the dependency in FastAPI:\n\n```python\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, Depends\nfrom jwt_auth.dependencies import get_user_from_token\n\napp = FastAPI()\n\n@app.get(\"/users/me\")\ndef read_users_me(current_user: str = Depends(get_user_from_token)):\n    return {\"user\": current_user}\n```\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "jwt_auth.exceptions", "documentation": ["jwt_auth/exceptions.py"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "jwt_auth.exceptions.AuthError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [{"name": "jwt_auth.exceptions.AuthError.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "detail", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "jwt_auth.dependencies", "documentation": ["jwt_auth/dependencies.py"], "functions": [{"n